Imaging of adenomatous hyperplastic lesions containing and not containing hepatocellular carcinoma in the liver. In 41 patients with 54 lesions which were resected ans studied histopathologically, there were 14 lesions of adenomatous hyperplasias (AH) in 9 patients, 28 AHs containing hepatocellular carcinoma foci (early HCC, e-HCC) in 22 and 12 borderline lesions which fell between these two lesions in 10. The detectability of these lesions on imagings was evaluated. Detection rates for all lesions and e-HCCs were as follows intraoperative sonography, 70.0%, 87.5%